content: Good gameplay and art! Sometimes there are server issues that make online games disappear from the list "My Games"... This is the only negative point I can see now.

I got this thinking it would be like dixit, or a simplified mysterium. I wasn't entirely wrong. But it would be better to compare this to codenames. Its quick and easy to learn, and fun. The only downside being if you don't have a person in your household to play with, you may have to sit and wait for a random person... all and all well worth the price of admission.

I really like the game. The lack of an AI means a long wait for others to play. It was, however, enough to convince me I need to get a copy of Similo Animals for my family, when it comes to hard copy.
